tern continues through s16. This means the knowledge file has doubled the section count unnecessarily—each source H2 should map to one knowledge section, not two. The empty sections s3, s5, s7, s9, s11, s13, and s15 are the problematic ones.\n\nThere's also a minor grammatical discrepancy in s6 where the source says \"大規模基幹システムを想定される可用性\" but the knowledge file has \"大規模基幹システムを想定した可用性\", though this is probably not significant enough to flag as a real issue.\n\nThe main structural problem remains those empty \"なし\" sections that don't align with the source content. Let me verify there aren't any actual content omissions by checking each section against the source material. The real issue is that there are seven empty \"なし\" sections interspersed throughout the knowledge file that don't correspond to anything in the source material—they're just padding the section count artificially from 9 up to 16. This structural bloat is what I should flag as my main finding.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16648,"cache_read_input_tokens":18561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":16648,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"79eb5f20-2790-49c3-845c-56d7c81032bf","uuid":"4fe8cc2c-4af4-49e3-a8b3-c1a53122b0af"}
